50|$|Philip Pettit (b. 1945) has argued, in Republicanism: A Theory of Freedom and Government (1997), {{that the}} theory of social contract, classically based on {{the consent of the}} governed, should be modified. Instead of arguing for <b>explicit</b> <b>consent,</b> which can always be manufactured, Pettit argues that the absence of an {{effective}} rebellion against it is a contract's only legitimacy.|$|R
