5000|$|First, 36(1) {{provides}} that parties may refer cases to the Court (jurisdiction founded on [...] "special agreement" [...] or [...] "compromis"). This method {{is based on}} <b>explicit</b> <b>consent</b> rather than true compulsory jurisdiction. It is, perhaps, the most effective basis for the Court's jurisdiction because the parties concerned have a desire for the dispute to be resolved by the Court and are thus more likely {{to comply with the}} Court's judgment.|$|R
